The 35-year-old was arrested on Tuesday morning in Promise Land near Whenchville. CAPE TOWN - A Kuruman man has been arrested for dealing in hydro dagga worth more than R1.1 million. The 35-year-old was arrested on Tuesday morning in Promise Land near Whenchville. While conducting the raid, members also confiscated a TV, sander, grinder and drill machines suspected to have been stolen. The police's Brigadier Ramatseba said: “He was also arrested in connection with stolen property. He will appear before the magistrates court on Wednesday for the possession of dagga and stolen property.”